      • addFont

        public HSLFFontInfo addFont(FontInfo fontInfo)
        Add font with the given FontInfo configuration to the font collection. The returned FontInfo contains the HSLF specific details and the collection uniquely contains fonts based on their typeface, i.e. calling the method with FontInfo objects having the same name results in the same HSLFFontInfo reference.(${t_bad92e6338ee4f958b6a1d787f31c3be})
        Parameters:
        fontInfo - the FontInfo configuration, can be a instance of HSLFFontInfo, HSLFFontInfoPredefined or a custom implementation(${t_6f2adb3d490c4d80a504964d5d20b0ed})
        Returns:
        the register HSLFFontInfo object(${t_2857e836a03b4cb7a7b0ebb1dee8018f})
